<article id="post-266" class="post-266 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-fedora tag-firefox tag-opengl tag-wayland tag-webrender tag-x11 entry">

	<header class="entry-header">
		<h1 class="entry-title">Firefox &#8211; we&#8217;re finally getting HW acceleration on&nbsp;Linux</h1>				<div class="entry-meta">
			<span class="byline"><svg class="svg-icon" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true" role="img" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 24 24" version="1.1" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><path d="M12 12c2.21 0 4-1.79 4-4s-1.79-4-4-4-4 1.79-4 4 1.79 4 4 4zm0 2c-2.67 0-8 1.34-8 4v2h16v-2c0-2.66-5.33-4-8-4z"></path><path d="M0 0h24v24H0z" fill="none"></path></svg><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted by</span><span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="https://mastransky.wordpress.com/author/komatisko/">Martin Stransky</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><svg class="svg-icon" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true" role="img" focusable="false" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><defs><path id="a" d="M0 0h24v24H0V0z"></path></defs><clipPath id="b"><use xlink:href="#a" overflow="visible"></use></clipPath><path clip-path="url(#b)" d="M12 2C6.5 2 2 6.5 2 12s4.5 10 10 10 10-4.5 10-10S17.5 2 12 2zm4.2 14.2L11 13V7h1.5v5.2l4.5 2.7-.8 1.3z"></path></svg><a href="https://mastransky.wordpress.com/2021/01/10/firefox-were-finally-getting-hw-acceleration-on-linux/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published" datetime="2021-01-10T20:40:25+00:00">January 10, 2021</time><time class="updated" datetime="2021-01-13T08:28:55+00:00">January 13, 2021</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><svg class="svg-icon" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true" role="img" focusable="false" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M10 4H4c-1.1 0-1.99.9-1.99 2L2 18c0 1.1.9 2 2 2h16c1.1 0 2-.9 2-2V8c0-1.1-.9-2-2-2h-8l-2-2z"></path><path d="M0 0h24v24H0z" fill="none"></path></svg><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted in</span><a href="https://mastransky.wordpress.com/category/fedora/" rel="category tag">Fedora</a></span><span class="tags-links"><svg class="svg-icon" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true" role="img" focusable="false" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M21.41 11.58l-9-9C12.05 2.22 11.55 2 11 2H4c-1.1 0-2 .9-2 2v7c0 .55.22 1.05.59 1.42l9 9c.36.36.86.58 1.41.58.55 0 1.05-.22 1.41-.59l7-7c.37-.36.59-.86.59-1.41 0-.55-.23-1.06-.59-1.42zM5.5 7C4.67 7 4 6.33 4 5.5S4.67 4 5.5 4 7 4.67 7 5.5 6.33 7 5.5 7z"></path><path d="M0 0h24v24H0z" fill="none"></path></svg><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags:</span><a href="https://mastransky.wordpress.com/tag/firefox/" rel="tag">Firefox</a>, <a href="https://mastransky.wordpress.com/tag/opengl/" rel="tag">OpenGL</a>, <a href="https://mastransky.wordpress.com/tag/wayland/" rel="tag">Wayland</a>, <a href="https://mastransky.wordpress.com/tag/webrender/" rel="tag">webrender</a>, <a href="https://mastransky.wordpress.com/tag/x11/" rel="tag">X11</a></span>		</div><!-- .meta-info -->
			</header>

	
	<div class="entry-content">
		
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img data-attachment-id="279" data-permalink="https://mastransky.wordpress.com/01-768x459-1/" data-orig-file="https://mastransky.files.wordpress.com/2021/01/01-768x459-1.png" data-orig-size="768,459" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="01-768&#215;459-1" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://mastransky.files.wordpress.com/2021/01/01-768x459-1.png?w=300" data-large-file="https://mastransky.files.wordpress.com/2021/01/01-768x459-1.png?w=750" src="https://mastransky.files.wordpress.com/2021/01/01-768x459-1.png?w=768" alt="" class="wp-image-279" srcset="https://mastransky.files.wordpress.com/2021/01/01-768x459-1.png 768w, https://mastransky.files.wordpress.com/2021/01/01-768x459-1.png?w=150 150w, https://mastransky.files.wordpress.com/2021/01/01-768x459-1.png?w=300 300w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px" /><figcaption>A first image from original <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://hacks.mozilla.org/2017/10/the-whole-web-at-maximum-fps-how-webrender-gets-rid-of-jank/" target="_blank">WebRender article</a>. Published three years ago.</figcaption></figure>



<p>Firefox 84.0 is a big milestone for Firefox Linux development as it comes with HW acceleration by default for some Linux users. Stock Mozilla Firefox 84.0 enables WebRender (HW accelerated backend) for Gnome/X.org and Gnome/Wayland will be supported in Firefox 85.0. Fedora is bit ahead and enables WebRender for Gnome/Wayland in Firefox 84.0 too.</p>



<p>WebRender by default is restricted to AMD/Intel graphics cards as NVIDIA is known for various issues &#8211; both proprietary and Noveau drivers. </p>



<p>And why it&#8217;s enabled in Gnome only for now? For instance KDE is also a popular desktop environment. I think it&#8217;s because Gnome utilizes HW acceleration so when Gnome works on your box there&#8217;s assumption that Firefox will work too. KDE provides choices how to disable/restrict HW acceleration setup (for instance it supports disabled screen compositing) and it&#8217;s more difficult to cover various scenarios.</p>



<p>Another excluded group are XWayland users. It means you have Wayland as a desktop compositor but for some reasons you use X11 emulation layer and run Firefox as X11 application. It&#8217;s a valid scenario, Firefox with Wayland backend still suffers from some annoying bug, mostly related to popup windows.</p>



<p>But don&#8217;t worry, Mozilla folks are going to bring WebRender to the most Linux users on various desktops and graphics. Jan created a brief Linux <a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1663273#c80" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">WebRender state overview</a>. And you can help with it! Please check if you have <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/How_to_debug_Firefox_problems#Check_WebRedner" target="_blank">WebRender enabled</a> and eventually try to enable it. Test various web pages, video playback, WebGL and report your experience. You can use comments below or drop me a mail at <a href="mailto:stransky@redhat.com">stransky@redhat.com</a>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img data-attachment-id="276" data-permalink="https://mastransky.wordpress.com/2021/01/10/firefox-were-finally-getting-hw-acceleration-on-linux/webrender-about/" data-orig-file="https://mastransky.files.wordpress.com/2021/01/webrender-about.png" data-orig-size="1121,708" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="webrender-about" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://mastransky.files.wordpress.com/2021/01/webrender-about.png?w=300" data-large-file="https://mastransky.files.wordpress.com/2021/01/webrender-about.png?w=750" src="https://mastransky.files.wordpress.com/2021/01/webrender-about.png?w=1024" alt="" class="wp-image-276" srcset="https://mastransky.files.wordpress.com/2021/01/webrender-about.png?w=1024 1024w, https://mastransky.files.wordpress.com/2021/01/webrender-about.png?w=150 150w, https://mastransky.files.wordpress.com/2021/01/webrender-about.png?w=300 300w, https://mastransky.files.wordpress.com/2021/01/webrender-about.png?w=768 768w, https://mastransky.files.wordpress.com/2021/01/webrender-about.png 1121w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p></p>
