									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Just to clarify, the purpose of disabling compositing is to boost performance in applications such as video games. It doesn&#8217;t imply that you should stop using hardware-accelerated rendering.</p>
<p id="comment-like-15466" data-liked=comment-not-liked class="comment-likes comment-not-liked"><a href="https://mastransky.wordpress.com/2021/01/10/firefox-were-finally-getting-hw-acceleration-on-linux/?like_comment=15466&#038;_wpnonce=d605fb47ea" class="comment-like-link needs-login" rel="nofollow" data-blog="151695875"><span>Like</span></a><span id="comment-like-count-15466" class="comment-like-feedback">Like</span></p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

