				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Yes, I understand it. Unfortunately it leads to issues with transparency, like <a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1479135" rel="nofollow ugc">https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1479135</a> .<br />
Does the disabled compositing actually help when HW rasterization is used? </p>
<p id="comment-like-15469" data-liked=comment-not-liked class="comment-likes comment-not-liked"><a href="https://mastransky.wordpress.com/2021/01/10/firefox-were-finally-getting-hw-acceleration-on-linux/?like_comment=15469&#038;_wpnonce=c4264f9f90" class="comment-like-link needs-login" rel="nofollow" data-blog="151695875"><span>Like</span></a><span id="comment-like-count-15469" class="comment-like-feedback">Like</span></p>
