				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>You can create a new Firefox profile (see <a href="https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/How_to_debug_Firefox_problems?rd=Bug_info_Firefox#Create_a_new_profile" rel="nofollow ugc">https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/How_to_debug_Firefox_problems?rd=Bug_info_Firefox#Create_a_new_profile</a>) and you&#8217;ll get default values there. Check if WebRender is enabled at about:support.</p>
<p>You can also go to about:config and type webrender there. All bold lines are changed from default setup. You can revert them to default values by the arrow icon.</p>
<p id="comment-like-15473" data-liked=comment-not-liked class="comment-likes comment-not-liked"><a href="https://mastransky.wordpress.com/2021/01/10/firefox-were-finally-getting-hw-acceleration-on-linux/?like_comment=15473&#038;_wpnonce=edcd8aff9d" class="comment-like-link needs-login" rel="nofollow" data-blog="151695875"><span>Like</span></a><span id="comment-like-count-15473" class="comment-like-feedback">Like</span></p>
