				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I&#8217;ve tested it a couple of weeks ago and it uses tons of memory. I&#8217;ve seen others complaining as well.<br />
<em>Without</em> WebRenderer I have about 10 GBs of available memory at start up, as indicated by the free command.<br />
<em>With</em> WebRenderer enabled I had almost nothing and if I&#8217;m not mistaking the swap was also used a bit. Other than this, it wasn&#8217;t that bad.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m using XFCE on Fedora 33, the GPU is Intel HD 4000 (i7-3770) and I have 32 GBs of RAM. If I remember correctly I set <code>gfx.webrender.all=true</code><code> in <strong>about:config</strong> to force it on video card.</p>
<p id="comment-like-15483" data-liked=comment-not-liked class="comment-likes comment-not-liked"><a href="https://mastransky.wordpress.com/2021/01/10/firefox-were-finally-getting-hw-acceleration-on-linux/?like_comment=15483&#038;_wpnonce=8e28eae254" class="comment-like-link needs-login" rel="nofollow" data-blog="151695875"><span>Like</span></a><span id="comment-like-count-15483" class="comment-like-feedback">Like</span></p>
