				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>The Gnome/Intel/AMD was chosen in a first batch because it&#8217;s known to work and Firefox developers have this setup, nothing more. For instance my laptop (provided by Red Hat) has Intel integrated GPU so I know it works on that.</p>
<p>NVIDIA is known for issues (see <a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1650583" rel="nofollow ugc">https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1650583</a> or <a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1663273" rel="nofollow ugc">https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1663273</a>) and it&#8217;s difficult and frustrating to debug closed sources drivers.</p>
<p id="comment-like-15490" data-liked=comment-not-liked class="comment-likes comment-not-liked"><a href="https://mastransky.wordpress.com/2021/01/10/firefox-were-finally-getting-hw-acceleration-on-linux/?like_comment=15490&#038;_wpnonce=6c3b46c600" class="comment-like-link needs-login" rel="nofollow" data-blog="151695875"><span>Like</span></a><span id="comment-like-count-15490" class="comment-like-feedback">Like</span></p>
