				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Hello,<br />
looking at <a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1663273#c80" rel="nofollow ugc">https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1663273#c80</a> as of Firefox 86 it seems like all known problems with KDE (either with or without compositing) are fixed. However, in my system (running Firefox 86 under Kubuntu 20.04) hardware compositing and web render are still both disabled by default. When do you plan to enable them by default for KDE? I&#8217;m running an Intel HD Graphics 4600, using X11.<br />
Thank you!</p>
<p id="comment-like-15862" data-liked=comment-not-liked class="comment-likes comment-not-liked"><a href="https://mastransky.wordpress.com/2021/01/10/firefox-were-finally-getting-hw-acceleration-on-linux/?like_comment=15862&#038;_wpnonce=03a5f16528" class="comment-like-link needs-login" rel="nofollow" data-blog="151695875"><span>Like</span></a><span id="comment-like-count-15862" class="comment-like-feedback">Like</span></p>
